#
# .hypatia-ignore — repo-scoped exemptions for the estate governance
# bundle's anti-pattern scanner. Format (per the bundle's `is_exempt`
# function): each non-comment line is `${rule}:${path}` matched as a
# fixed-string whole-line equality (`grep -qxF`).
#
# Comment lines (`#`) and blank lines are tolerated because they never
# match the `rule:path` shape under -xF.

# ─── Gossamer's vendored Android platform shell (third_party/) ─────────
#
# third_party/gossamer/android/src/main/java/io/gossamer/{GossamerActivity,
# GossamerBridge}.java are part of the vendored Gossamer webview shell
# (third_party/gossamer/), not paint-type's own source. The estate's
# "Kotlin is goodbye" policy targets hand-written JVM bindings written
# BY a project's own FFI/interop layer; Android's platform contract
# itself requires a JVM-hosted Activity + WebView bridge class regardless
# of implementation language underneath (Gossamer's own core is Zig/Rust
# per its architecture — these two files are the unavoidable Android
# platform glue, not a policy violation of paint-type's own tier mapping).
# Rewriting vendored upstream code to route around a shell policy is out
# of scope and not owned by paint-type; the exemption travels with the
# vendored copy.
cicd_rules/banned_language_file:third_party/gossamer/android/src/main/java/io/gossamer/GossamerActivity.java
